description: The default benchmarking scenarios to stress-test an AMQP server

groups.name: Throughput to an Unsubscribed Topic
groups.description: A single producer sending non-persistent messages to a topic that does not have an consumers attached.

groups.name: Queue Throughput
groups.description: 1 producer and 1 consumer connected to a queue.

groups.name: Topic Throughput
groups.description: 1 producer and 1 consumer connected to a topic.

groups.name: Reliable Queue Fan In/Out Load Scenarios
groups.description:
Multiple consumers and producers communicate via one shared Queue. 
      All messages sent have a 20 byte payload.
      All messages are sent reliably by marking them persistent and 
      and using at least once semantics when sending over the messaging links.

groups.name: Reliable Topic Scale Out
groups.description:
Multiple consumers and producers communicate via one shared Topic. 
      All messages sent have a 20 byte payload.
      All messages are sent reliably by marking them persistent and 
      and using at least once semantics when sending over the messaging links.

groups.name: Un-reliable Queue Scale Out
groups.description:
Multiple consumers and producers communicate via one shared Queue. 
      All messages sent have a 20 byte payload.
      All messages are sent unreliably by marking them non-persistent and 
      and using at most once semantics when sending over the messaging links.

groups.name: Unreliable Topic Scale Out
groups.description:
Multiple consumers and producers communicate via one shared Topic. 
      All messages sent have a 20 byte payload.
      All messages are sent unreliably by marking them non-persistent and 
      and using at most once semantics when sending over the messaging links.
